HEADWORD: Mismate
<hw>Mis*mate"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <def>To mate wrongly
or unsuitably; to mismatch; <as>as, to <ex>mismate</ex> gloves or shoes;
a <ex>mismated</ex> couple.</as></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

